AB In light of the increasing interest in hedonic aspects of consumer
   behavior, it is clear that consumer taste plays a critical role in
   judgment and decision making, particularly for hedonic products and
   services. At the present time, however, our understanding of consumer
   aesthetic taste and its specific role for consumer behavior is limited.
   In this article, we review the literature from a variety of fields such
   as sociology, psychology, philosophy, and consumer behavior in order to
   develop a conceptual definition of consumer aesthetic taste. We then
   explore various issues related to taste and develop a conceptual
